# DEPLOYMENT SETUP GUIDE

## For Local Development
Use the `.env` files in both `backend/` and `frontend/` folders

### Backend Local (.env)
PORT=8081
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:8081/api/auth/google/callback

### Frontend Local (.env)
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8081
VITE_REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8081/api

## For Production Deployment

### Step 1: Deploy Backend to Render
1. Get your Render URL (e.g., https://jobportal-backend.onrender.com)
2. Update `backend/.env.production`:
   - CORS_ORIGIN=https://your-vercel-frontend-url.vercel.app
   - GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=https://jobportal-backend.onrender.com/api/auth/google/callback
   - FRONTEND_URL=https://your-vercel-frontend-url.vercel.app

### Step 2: Deploy Frontend to Vercel
1. Get your Vercel URL (e.g., https://jobportal.vercel.app)
2. Update `frontend/.env.production`:
   - VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://jobportal-backend.onrender.com
   - VITE_REACT_APP_API_URL=https://jobportal-backend.onrender.com/api

### Step 3: Update Render Environment Variables
In Render dashboard, add these environment variables:
- Same content from `backend/.env.production`

### Step 4: Update Vercel Environment Variables
In Vercel dashboard, add these environment variables:
- Same content from `frontend/.env.production`

## Important Notes
- `.env` = Local development
- `.env.production` = Production/Deployment
- Keep sensitive keys safe, never commit real keys to git
- Update URLs in .env.production with your actual deployed URLs
